So Ive decided that not only is this the end of high school, and the end of my life as I have always known it, but its the end of every relationship I have ever established. The way I see it, I have my friends right now, but once we all move that friendship ends, as we will all go our seperate ways. I feel the only way to truly know who your friends are, is by cutting every single one loose. Ive gotten to the point with everyone in Venice that if they want my friendship, they are gonna have to work their asses off to get it. Im a pretty awesome fucking friend, I have thrown away so much shit for these people, and Im watching as they just, not only ignore it, but the bond in general. Ive been lied to more times than I can count, and its ironic that its been from the people I have known the longest. I feel like Im almost dead from this suffication. I love my friends, I really do, but I've got to get away from this unwavering egotism. Ill say it, some of them, Ive never met anyone more intelligent, more eloquent, more intuned with people and the lives of everyone around them. So why is it that they feel the need to ruin their intellect with presriptions, and  benzoylmethyl ecognine, and THC, i dont see the attraction. Sure ill burn once in a while, and ive been known to put shit up my nose, but for christ sake, grow up, and see how much there is to life. You of all people know, but you just neglect everything around you. Maybe its this town, maybe its just that its too hard to find something more productive. But regardless of what is it, this shouldnt be the reason why I have been ostrasized from your life. Its flattering to know that your love for snorting, smoking, eating, chewing, and injecting, has outdone my love for you. But im done. Done with the drugs, done with trying to make you see, done with trying to see for myself, done with acting like your mothers, done with holding your head, done with checking your pulse, done with spotting you cash, done with trying to make you love me, and make you see that im here. Because im not anymore. I just cant be.

Last night a room full drunk sang along to the songs I never had the courage to write....given the chance I'd stay in this chorus forever, where everything ugly in this world is sadly beautiful...in our desperate memories. No we're not going to call everyone on their shit tonight. even though the half of you won't even smile the next time we pass on the street. Maybe somehow this scam will still save us all...and I saw you dancing at a punk rock show, and for a moment we walked streets that everyone else had given up to 4am. Curse promises and spray paint marking everywhere we went. And every direction only going as far as we let it. There's so many things we tried to do truthfully. By the time it's through with us it all falls apart. Maybe somehow this scam will still save us all.
